{
  "texts": [
    "Distinct past encounters with others can have long-lasting effects on one's actions, which can be described as \"invisible but nonetheless felt 'real presences' (Steiner 1989)\" (Shotter 2003: 359).",
    "Their agentic influences determine how people engage in and with aspects of the world.",
    "But how do these presences of absent people (such as a mother's voice) emerge and affect people's daily activities?",
    "And how can they possibly be traced?",
    "In this paper, I refer to the phenomenon of re-evoking one's past encounters with other people as human presencing."
  ]
}